This paper discusses the theory of error in cross-validation testing of algorithms for predicting real-valued attributes. This topic is closely related to machine learning and statistical analysis, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. Specifically, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.ST (Statistics) are the most likely categories, as they directly relate to the topic of the paper. Additionally, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also possible categories, as they are related to the implementation and optimization of machine learning algorithms.
